GZIP : 

    COMPRESS FILES : gzip File_1 File_N

    READ GZIP FILE : zcat Filename

    GREP ON GZIP FILE : zgrep Filename

    DECOMPRESS GZIP FILE : 
    
        gzip -d Filename
        gunzip File_1 File_N

    ZIP WHILE KEEPING ORIGINAL UNZIPPED : gzip -k Filename

    COMPRESSION to LEVEL (1 TO 9) Nth : gzip -vN Filename

    LIST INFO OF ZIP FILE : gzip -l Filename

    GZIP ALL FILES IN A DIRECTORY : gzip -r Directory/Path

    RENAME OR APPEND WHILE ZIPPING FILE : gzip -c Filename >> NewFileName


TAR : 

    CREATE TAR FILE : 
        
        tar --create --file="Tar_File_name.tar" File_1 File_2 File_N Folder
        tar -cvf Tar_File_name.tar File_1 File_2 File_N Folder

    LIST TAR FILE CONTENTS : 

        tar --list --file="Tar_File_name.tar" 
        tar -tf Tar_File_name.tar
        tar --list -f Tar_File_name.tar
        tar -tvf Tar_File_name.tar

    EXTRACT TAR FILE : tar -xf Tar_File_name.tar